The paper focuses on applying natural language processing techniques to code analysis, which is a common topic in software engineering (cs.SE). The proposed method involves learning a representation of code semantics, which is a machine learning task (cs.LG). The paper also mentions using an Intermediate Representation (IR) of the code, which is a common topic in programming languages (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing embeddings qualitatively using analogies and clustering, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
